        <Param val="True" valType="bool" updates="None" name="syncScreenRefresh"/>
        <Param val="Potential Harms, Risks or Discomforts: There are no known risks to this study beyond those naturally occurring in everyday life. The decibel level of the sounds used will be within the range of those encountered in everyday speech. You do not need to answer questions that you do not want to answer or that make you feel uncomfortable, and you can withdraw (stop taking part) at any time.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Potential Benefits: The research will not benefit you directly. However, we hope it will be useful in gaining a better understanding of the way that we hear and use sound in everyday life. This may be informative in improving the way we listen to music and/or engage in verbal communication. Additionally, it may help inform clinical treatments designed to assist those struggling with certain aspects of auditory perception.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Payment or Reimbursement: For your participation today, you will receive 1 course credit through Sona. If for any reason you wish to withdraw from the experiment, you may do so at any time, without consequence. You may also remove your data from the study for any reason, without any consequences. If you decide to withdraw or remove your data, you will still receive full participation credit or payment, regardless of completion.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Confidentiality: The information gathered about you and from you in this study will be kept confidential and private. Your name and other identification will be available only to the principal investigator and members of the investigator’s research team. To this end, every participant will be assigned an ID number, and the only document linking your name with this ID number will be stored in a locked cabinet, and/or in a password protected file on a computer in a locked laboratory, Hard copies of this data will be kept on file for seven (7) years, after which they will be destroyed. Electronic copies of the data (which will not include any identifying information), may be kept indefinitely.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Participation and Withdrawal: If you decide to be part of the study, you can decide to stop (withdraw), at any time, even after signing the consent form or part-way through the study. If you decide to withdraw, there will be no consequences. In cases of withdrawal, any data you have provided will be destroyed unless you indicate otherwise. If you do not want to answer some of the background questions, you can leave them blank and still participate in other aspects of the study.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Press SPACE to continue..." valType="str" updates="constant" name="text"/>
        <Param val="from exp settings" valType="str" updates="None" name="units"/>
        <Param val="" valType="code" updates="None" name="validator"/>
        <Param val="" valType="num" updates="constant" name="wrapWidth"/>
      </TextComponent>
